=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Suzuki couple 1-bromo-2-iodo-4-nitrobenzene with cyclohex-1-en-1-yl boronic acid (or Bpin) to give 1-bromo-2-(cyclohex-1-en-1-yl)-4-nitrobenzene | Step 2: Pd-catalyzed α-arylation of methyl tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-carboxylate with that aryl bromide to form methyl 4-[2-(cyclohex-1-en-1-yl)-4-nitrophenyl]tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-carboxylate | Step 3: Reduce NO2 to NH2 (H2/Pd-C or Fe/HCl) to obtain methyl 4-[4-amino-2-(cyclohex-1-en-1-yl)phenyl]tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-carboxylate | Step 4: Prepare the heteroaryl acid fragment by O-alkylating the corresponding hydroxymethyl acid HOOC-c1nc(C#N)cn1CH2OH with 2-bromoethyltrimethylsilane (or 2-trimethylsilylethyl sulfonate) to give HOOC-c1nc(C#N)cn1CH2OCH2CH2Si(CH3)3 | Step 5: Activate this acid (SOCl2 or HATU) and acylate the aniline from Step 3 to furnish COC(=O)C1(c2ccc(NC(=O)c3nc(C#N)cn3COCC[Si](C)(C)C)c(C3=CCCCC3)c2)CCOCC1.

